BS, IV, 251 (P. Gini).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1184">In hagiography: Constantine was a bishop
            of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/118">Laodicea</placeName>. He was a friend
            of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/51">Severus of Antioch</persName> and was
          present at many of the meetings of the Miaphysites that took place in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/586">Constantinople</placeName>. He was a principal author
          of the <title>canons of the Miaphysite community</title> from the sixth century.</note>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib1184-1">
